Patch Set 7: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(1 inline comment)

I am not 100% sure what you are going for here, can you explain the goal in a bit more detail?  

Here are a few commands that I ran that failed:

$ glance-manage db_sync --version
usage: glance-manage [options] <cmd>
glance-manage: error: unrecognized arguments: --version

$ glance-manage db --version downgrade 9
usage: glance-manage [options] <cmd>
glance-manage: error: unrecognized arguments: --version

$ glance-manage db --version upgrade 10
usage: glance-manage [options] <cmd>
glance-manage: error: unrecognized arguments: --version

Is the idea for the options to be allowed at any place in the command?  If so this patch has problems.  If not I do not understand what the goal is exactly.
